*Databases- systems that allow users to store & organize data, helpful when dealing with large amounts of data, data integrity,
handle massive amounts of data, combine datasets, automate steps for re-use
*Spreadsheets- one time analysis, quick chart, reasonable data size (tabs = tables in database)
*types of database platforms- PostgreSQL, MySQL, MariaSQL, etc.
*SQL(Structured Query Language)- language to communicate with our database
*MOST commands are general SQL
*PostgreSQL - SQL engine that stores data and reads queries and returns information
*PgAdmin - Graphical User Interface for connecting with PostgreSQL
*Remember PostgreSQL password
